1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:13,885 --> 00:00:16,855
(Seo Ji Hye)

3
00:00:21,625 --> 00:00:24,365
(Go Soo)

4
00:00:30,505 --> 00:00:33,475
(Kim Jae Kyung)

5
00:00:38,345 --> 00:00:40,885
(Yoon Je Moon)

6
00:00:47,225 --> 00:00:51,155
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

7
00:00:54,125 --> 00:00:56,065
(Characters, places, and events are not real.)

8
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:58,645
(Children and animals were filmed under production guidelines.)

9
00:01:01,665 --> 00:01:02,825
What are you going to do now?

10
00:01:04,135 --> 00:01:08,405
The way Myo Jin found out about us, it's not like you think.

11
00:01:09,105 --> 00:01:12,945
It's not like the memory came back to her naturally over time.

12
00:01:14,015 --> 00:01:15,215
That makes no sense.

13
00:01:16,445 --> 00:01:18,155
She's been digging around,

14
00:01:19,285 --> 00:01:22,025
meeting with all sorts of people. That's how she found out.

15
00:01:24,325 --> 00:01:27,065
I never imagined she'd find out this quickly.

16
00:01:28,125 --> 00:01:29,265
What's important is...

17
00:01:29,995 --> 00:01:32,465
she's not going to just let this go.

18
00:01:36,165 --> 00:01:37,175
Then...

19
00:01:38,005 --> 00:01:39,375
what am I supposed to do?

20
00:01:40,305 --> 00:01:41,305
Stop her!

21
00:01:42,075 --> 00:01:43,075
But...

22
00:01:44,015 --> 00:01:45,045
is that even possible?

23
00:01:47,485 --> 00:01:50,015
Do you think we have the luxury of second-guessing this?

24
00:01:50,785 --> 00:01:54,425
What do you think will happen to us if she pushes this any further?

25
00:01:56,185 --> 00:01:57,945
She cannot be allowed to take one more step.

26
00:01:59,025 --> 00:02:01,995
You don't have a choice. Protecting Myo Jin...

27
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:04,295
means protecting all of us.

28
00:02:07,705 --> 00:02:09,105
You look conflicted.

29
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:11,375
Why?

30
00:02:11,975 --> 00:02:12,975
Losing your nerve?

31
00:02:14,645 --> 00:02:19,275
- Fine, should I just give up? - Shut it!

32
00:02:50,975 --> 00:02:52,695
So you don't care that the Chairman's dead,

33
00:02:53,115 --> 00:02:55,745
and you're going to take your cut and run? Is that it?

34
00:02:56,145 --> 00:02:58,065
You think I don't know what you're really after?

35
00:02:58,585 --> 00:03:00,185
The jerk who did that to the Chairman...

36
00:03:00,655 --> 00:03:04,525
If the police can't find him, I'll find him myself!

37
00:03:04,795 --> 00:03:08,125
And I already have someone in mind. You scum!

38
00:03:22,345 --> 00:03:25,415
(Caught)

39
00:03:26,715 --> 00:03:28,585
Yes, I know.

40
00:03:29,415 --> 00:03:31,695
Just keep an eye on the situation for a bit longer. Okay.

41
00:03:32,015 --> 00:03:34,625
Okay, I'm calling in that favour. Yes.

42
00:03:40,265 --> 00:03:44,065
It's a relief. He's in the ICU, but it's not life-threatening.

43
00:03:47,535 --> 00:03:49,565
But are you okay?

44
00:03:52,275 --> 00:03:54,645
I told him I was a cop, and he still hit me?

45
00:03:56,175 --> 00:03:57,775
Just wait until he wakes up.

46
00:03:58,345 --> 00:04:00,145
I'll put him right back in this hospital bed.

47
00:04:02,645 --> 00:04:05,154
Anyway, business is business.

48
00:04:05,155 --> 00:04:06,955
Let's see. Did you get a clean copy?

49
00:04:08,885 --> 00:04:13,395
- Here. - Yes. I had it all timed out.

50
00:04:14,025 --> 00:04:15,995
That should've been more than enough time.

51
00:04:16,525 --> 00:04:18,095
Go ahead and check it.

52
00:04:18,895 --> 00:04:21,135
There's nothing much on the phone.

53
00:04:21,765 --> 00:04:23,285
We just need to see the text messages.

54
00:04:23,675 --> 00:04:25,151
You said her name was Hee Soo, right?

55
00:04:25,175 --> 00:04:26,505
Yes, Choi Hee Soo.

56
00:04:26,675 --> 00:04:30,145
We'll find out once we see what the two of them were texting about.

57
00:04:30,575 --> 00:04:33,915
What on earth they were trying so desperately to hide.

58
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:36,285
And how you're involved in all this.

59
00:04:37,155 --> 00:04:39,985
Choi Hee Soo.

60
00:04:41,255 --> 00:04:43,085
Choi Hee Soo... Yes!

61
00:04:43,755 --> 00:04:44,955
Here she is! Choi Hee Soo!

62
00:04:46,055 --> 00:04:47,065
Okay.

63
00:04:47,095 --> 00:04:48,395
(Choi Hee Soo)

64
00:04:48,595 --> 00:04:50,835
Just as I thought. She was being blackmailed.

65
00:04:51,635 --> 00:04:55,565
But all of these are just messages telling her to do as she's told.

66
00:04:56,065 --> 00:04:59,035
- Usually, they demand money. - Oh, here.

67
00:04:59,575 --> 00:05:01,815
From this point on, Lee Jong Su's name keeps popping up.

68
00:05:02,045 --> 00:05:03,174
Let's see.

69
00:05:03,175 --> 00:05:04,215
Oh, here!

70
00:05:05,115 --> 00:05:08,115
I knew it. That jerk. What, 300,000 dollars?

71
00:05:08,885 --> 00:05:09,885
In one go?

72
00:05:10,955 --> 00:05:13,355
What? They must have had some serious dirt on her.

73
00:05:13,725 --> 00:05:16,055
- There's no other explanation. - Scroll down some more.

74
00:05:17,455 --> 00:05:21,825
This guy keeps threatening her even after he got paid. What's this?

75
00:05:22,725 --> 00:05:25,765
But here, he's sending pictures of some man.

76
00:05:26,365 --> 00:05:27,765
Is this also part of the blackmail?

77
00:05:30,175 --> 00:05:31,175
Wait, this is...

78
00:05:31,975 --> 00:05:33,775
What the... Wait...

79
00:05:34,445 --> 00:05:36,975
But why is this here? Wait...

80
00:05:40,545 --> 00:05:41,585
Gosh, this is...

81
00:05:42,785 --> 00:05:45,415
So that's how it was?

82
00:05:58,035 --> 00:05:59,465
He'll put a lot of care into it.

83
00:05:59,735 --> 00:06:03,705
I may have pressured him a bit, you know, for my daughter's gallery.

84
00:06:04,735 --> 00:06:07,245
Coming from an assemblyman up for his fifth term,

85
00:06:08,005 --> 00:06:09,205
I'm sure he'll do a fine job.

86
00:06:10,645 --> 00:06:13,815
In my experience, the contractors who flock to politicians...

87
00:06:14,345 --> 00:06:15,815
are rarely on the level.

88
00:06:16,415 --> 00:06:18,215
What, a "contractor"?

89
00:06:18,785 --> 00:06:21,525
He's a C-level executive in the Korean architecture industry.

90
00:06:22,885 --> 00:06:25,055
I don't know how close you two are,

91
00:06:25,925 --> 00:06:28,205
but is it really okay to be asking for a favour like this?

92
00:06:28,565 --> 00:06:30,495
The construction costs look astronomical too.

93
00:06:31,365 --> 00:06:33,535
Don't you think your father knows what he's doing?

94
00:06:35,435 --> 00:06:36,435
Wait.

95
00:06:37,005 --> 00:06:39,405
What brings you here so suddenly, Representative Jo?

96
00:06:40,445 --> 00:06:42,351
Something urgent came up that I need to discuss with you,

97
00:06:42,375 --> 00:06:44,145
and I heard you were here.

98
00:06:44,415 --> 00:06:46,375
Is that so? Please, have a seat.

99
00:06:52,815 --> 00:06:54,385
So, what did you need to discuss?

100
00:06:54,555 --> 00:06:57,555
It's just as you suspected.

101
00:06:57,695 --> 00:07:00,665
It appears Oh Sang Il did in fact meet with Ryu Jun Ho.

102
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:04,535
So they did meet in secret. Ryu Jun Ho and that guy.

103
00:07:05,065 --> 00:07:08,765
Now, I can personally let this slide,

104
00:07:08,835 --> 00:07:11,475
but if word of this ever got out,

105
00:07:12,435 --> 00:07:14,915
it could tarnish the reputation of the competition's sponsors.

106
00:07:18,675 --> 00:07:22,345
You're a bit late with this, aren't you?

107
00:07:22,845 --> 00:07:27,425
- Sir? - Yesterday, sponsors discussed...

108
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:31,525
a new internal regulation, as I understand it.

109
00:07:32,895 --> 00:07:35,595
And apparently, it was at Oh Sang Il's strong request.

110
00:07:37,265 --> 00:07:40,965
Finding what that is seems vital, don't you think?

111
00:07:47,975 --> 00:07:50,475
Look, people make mistakes sometimes.

112
00:07:51,045 --> 00:07:53,015
They get ripped off. It happens.

113
00:07:53,415 --> 00:07:55,695
Gosh, why'd he have to get tangled up in a love triangle?

114
00:07:55,815 --> 00:08:00,485
No use crying over spilled milk. Just clean up and don't do it again.

115
00:08:04,725 --> 00:08:06,425
You can't avoid the first arrow,

116
00:08:06,995 --> 00:08:09,125
but they say you should never be hit by the second.

117
00:08:09,465 --> 00:08:12,894
- Don't let this get to you so... - Lee Jong Su...

118
00:08:12,895 --> 00:08:15,175
- Gosh, you startled me. - Why was he tormenting Hee Soo?

119
00:08:15,335 --> 00:08:17,255
What do you mean, why? For the money, of course.

120
00:08:17,305 --> 00:08:19,865
You saw it yourself. He squeezed a fortune out of her in one go.

121
00:08:19,935 --> 00:08:20,945
No.

122
00:08:21,475 --> 00:08:23,575
- It wasn't about the money. - It wasn't?

123
00:08:23,645 --> 00:08:24,915
Hee Soo is the victim here.

124
00:08:25,675 --> 00:08:29,345
If he used the photos for blackmail, it shouldn't have been Hee Soo.

125
00:08:29,615 --> 00:08:32,755
Blackmailing us would make sense if money was his only motive?

126
00:08:33,655 --> 00:08:34,655
You have a point.

127
00:08:35,925 --> 00:08:37,755
Lee Jong Su must have had another reason.

128
00:08:38,355 --> 00:08:39,925
And that's what Hee Soo was afraid of.

129
00:08:41,395 --> 00:08:43,155
It wasn't about my relationship with Jun Ho.

130
00:08:44,535 --> 00:08:46,815
It was another reason, one that scared Hee Soo even more.

131
00:09:09,055 --> 00:09:10,055
Here you go.

132
00:09:13,095 --> 00:09:14,525
Gosh, a hamburger!

133
00:09:15,265 --> 00:09:17,235
It's getting late. Go on inside.

134
00:09:18,165 --> 00:09:19,925
And make sure to save some for your brother.

135
00:09:24,605 --> 00:09:25,605
Mister.

136
00:09:26,475 --> 00:09:27,475
Yes?

137
00:09:27,745 --> 00:09:29,375
Mister, are you rich?

138
00:09:30,205 --> 00:09:31,775
- Rich? - Yes.

139
00:09:33,575 --> 00:09:35,685
Of course I am.

140
00:09:36,385 --> 00:09:37,785
How rich are you?

141
00:09:38,755 --> 00:09:42,725
Enough to buy you one of these every single day.

142
00:09:43,255 --> 00:09:44,255
Goodness!

143
00:09:45,925 --> 00:09:48,925
But Mister, where'd you get all that money?

144
00:09:50,565 --> 00:09:53,905
How do I get rich like you?

145
00:10:20,765 --> 00:10:21,795
Who are you people?

146
00:10:24,365 --> 00:10:25,365
Hello?

147
00:10:57,995 --> 00:10:58,995
Hey.

148
00:11:01,005 --> 00:11:02,305
All right, that's enough.

149
00:11:02,705 --> 00:11:06,675
You're taking it too far. Do you have to be so crude?

150
00:11:07,545 --> 00:11:09,305
Have some common sense, for crying out loud.

151
00:11:10,075 --> 00:11:13,115
I think he gets the picture by now, don't you?

152
00:11:14,815 --> 00:11:16,315
A smart and perceptive man like...

153
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:18,615
our CEO Ryu.

154
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:24,755
Isn't that right?

155
00:11:25,825 --> 00:11:28,595
CEO Ryu Jun Ho of Mono Architecture.

156
00:11:35,905 --> 00:11:37,375
That hit a nerve, didn't it?

157
00:11:38,605 --> 00:11:40,565
Did you think you could do that behind my back...

158
00:11:41,045 --> 00:11:42,475
and nobody would find out?

159
00:11:43,245 --> 00:11:45,615
The stink is spreading in all directions.

160
00:11:47,685 --> 00:11:49,685
Back off from this competition.

161
00:11:50,955 --> 00:11:52,315
Consider this a warning.

162
00:11:52,985 --> 00:11:55,285
If I hear your name come up again,

163
00:11:56,085 --> 00:11:57,085
then...

164
00:11:58,925 --> 00:12:01,065
that handsome face we left untouched today...

165
00:12:04,065 --> 00:12:05,535
There won't be anything left of it.

166
00:12:10,235 --> 00:12:11,335
All right, let's go.

167
00:12:22,815 --> 00:12:23,955
Hey, long time no see.

168
00:12:25,485 --> 00:12:28,625
Man, you can pack it away. Two servings gone in a flash.

169
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:34,025
But is it really that important where Detective Gang is?

170
00:12:34,425 --> 00:12:37,065
Of course not. What's he going to do on his own?

171
00:12:37,995 --> 00:12:41,205
- Then why... - Because I owe you.

172
00:12:42,705 --> 00:12:45,675
And now, there's something you need to tell me.

173
00:12:47,075 --> 00:12:49,345
- Sir? - What's up with Detective Gang?

174
00:12:49,705 --> 00:12:51,815
He didn't just drop the villa case for no reason.

175
00:12:56,645 --> 00:12:57,685
I wouldn't know.

176
00:12:58,215 --> 00:12:59,215
Come on.

177
00:12:59,715 --> 00:13:00,924
Wasn't it Detective Gang who trained you...

178
00:13:00,925 --> 00:13:02,585
when you first started here?

179
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:04,155
I...

180
00:13:05,155 --> 00:13:07,325
practically raised Detective Gang.

181
00:13:12,095 --> 00:13:13,795
A month before Detective Gang quit,

182
00:13:14,505 --> 00:13:16,235
you two got hammered together, right?

183
00:13:16,905 --> 00:13:18,105
What did you two talk about?

184
00:13:18,905 --> 00:13:21,645
If I say something I shouldn't and it blows up...

185
00:13:22,505 --> 00:13:23,805
Hey. Look at me.

186
00:13:26,175 --> 00:13:27,585
It's because I need your help.

187
00:13:28,115 --> 00:13:30,215
We need to get Detective Gang back, don't we?

188
00:13:38,325 --> 00:13:41,265
Detective Gang didn't just quit.

189
00:13:41,965 --> 00:13:44,965
When we were drinking, he kept saying he trusted no one.

190
00:13:46,395 --> 00:13:50,435
He said he found something important but couldn't act on it himself yet.

191
00:13:50,505 --> 00:13:52,475
- What was it? - I honestly don't know.

192
00:13:55,445 --> 00:13:59,645
He'd rather take it to his grave than reveal it half-cocked.

193
00:14:21,565 --> 00:14:22,565
It's empty.

194
00:14:51,535 --> 00:14:52,665
Have you been watching me?

195
00:14:53,265 --> 00:14:54,985
You looked like you had a lot on your mind.

196
00:14:56,205 --> 00:14:57,935
And I had some things to think about too.

197
00:15:02,075 --> 00:15:04,115
During field day in elementary school,

198
00:15:04,415 --> 00:15:06,815
there was this event called the "find-a-person" race.

199
00:15:08,145 --> 00:15:09,645
I thought it was so much fun.

200
00:15:11,515 --> 00:15:13,435
I was always a really confident runner, you see.

201
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:17,555
But then it was my turn,

202
00:15:17,995 --> 00:15:21,165
I drew a slip of paper, and on it,

203
00:15:22,625 --> 00:15:24,265
it said, "Mom."

204
00:15:26,965 --> 00:15:29,365
I guess the person who wrote it couldn't have known...

205
00:15:30,165 --> 00:15:31,175
that of all people,

206
00:15:32,435 --> 00:15:36,505
a kid without a mom would be the one to draw it.

207
00:15:39,845 --> 00:15:40,845
At that moment,

208
00:15:41,545 --> 00:15:43,915
I think that's when it hit me.

209
00:15:45,785 --> 00:15:47,015
That rules...

210
00:15:48,955 --> 00:15:51,055
aren't made for the have-nots.

211
00:15:52,555 --> 00:15:55,225
They're made for the haves.

212
00:16:01,305 --> 00:16:04,475
That my parents hadn't gone to the US to make money,

213
00:16:05,905 --> 00:16:09,145
but actually died in an accident.

214
00:16:10,645 --> 00:16:12,485
I think I found that out around the same time.

215
00:16:15,785 --> 00:16:18,785
I'd been pestering my grandmother for days,

216
00:16:20,315 --> 00:16:21,635
begging her to tell me the truth.

217
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:23,955
So what did you do?

218
00:16:26,395 --> 00:16:29,075
I just grabbed the hand of some lady who looked like a mom and ran.

219
00:16:30,695 --> 00:16:32,035
The whole school was watching.

220
00:16:33,135 --> 00:16:36,065
And I didn't want anyone to find out I didn't have a mom.

221
00:16:45,715 --> 00:16:48,585
A man called Representative Jo came to see my dad today,

222
00:16:50,085 --> 00:16:51,585
and I heard him talking about you.

223
00:16:56,455 --> 00:16:57,555
That was him, wasn't it?

224
00:17:00,495 --> 00:17:01,975
Thanks to you, that clears things up.

225
00:17:03,425 --> 00:17:06,565
I was wondering what was going on...

226
00:17:08,305 --> 00:17:09,405
behind the scenes.

227
00:17:22,145 --> 00:17:24,485
I'm curious about the race that day.

228
00:17:32,155 --> 00:17:34,235
I ran like my life depended on it and came in first.

229
00:17:36,095 --> 00:17:37,395
I just didn't want to lose.

230
00:17:38,465 --> 00:17:39,665
Not in that situation.

231
00:17:40,695 --> 00:17:43,205
I bet winning that day felt extra special.

232
00:17:44,105 --> 00:17:45,275
Actually,

233
00:17:46,475 --> 00:17:48,375
I don't think it was quite like that.

234
00:18:08,025 --> 00:18:10,565
(El Karaoke Bar)

235
00:18:14,835 --> 00:18:16,075
Why isn't this jerk picking up?

236
00:18:16,565 --> 00:18:18,175
He usually answers right away.

237
00:18:18,675 --> 00:18:20,135
Is he really in the bar business?

238
00:18:20,975 --> 00:18:21,975
Yes.

239
00:18:23,445 --> 00:18:24,685
And this is how he runs things?

240
00:18:24,715 --> 00:18:27,415
I wouldn't know. My job is just to deliver the person and get paid.

241
00:18:31,815 --> 00:18:33,295
I'll try calling him again right now.

242
00:18:34,625 --> 00:18:36,955
Don't bother. He'll call us.

243
00:18:37,555 --> 00:18:40,555
Don't try anything funny. You just stay with us.

244
00:18:40,965 --> 00:18:42,495
What are you here for?

245
00:18:48,565 --> 00:18:49,565
Sir.

246
00:18:50,365 --> 00:18:51,925
Do you happen to live in this building?

247
00:18:52,075 --> 00:18:54,845
I run the lottery shop right out front.

248
00:18:56,805 --> 00:18:58,565
By the way, is this place open for business?

249
00:18:59,575 --> 00:19:01,921
I have a reunion with some friends from my hometown tomorrow,

250
00:19:01,945 --> 00:19:04,785
but it's closed. There'll be about 30 of us.

251
00:19:06,955 --> 00:19:09,725
This place is hardly ever open.

252
00:19:10,355 --> 00:19:11,825
The so-called owner...

253
00:19:12,355 --> 00:19:15,125
only crawls out to open up whenever he feels like it.

254
00:19:16,665 --> 00:19:19,835
But are there really 30 of you?

255
00:19:21,605 --> 00:19:22,845
We're all bringing our spouses.

256
00:19:23,865 --> 00:19:27,945
- What a shame. Let's go elsewhere. - Hey, hold on a second.

257
00:19:28,475 --> 00:19:29,845
I have his number.

258
00:19:32,615 --> 00:19:34,485
Calling himself a business owner...

259
00:19:34,745 --> 00:19:36,215
That darn runaway.

260
00:19:36,285 --> 00:19:40,055
- The customer is unavailable. - For crying out loud.

261
00:19:40,885 --> 00:19:42,885
I don't know why he even bothers carrying a phone.

262
00:19:44,725 --> 00:19:47,595
By the way... The way you talk...

263
00:19:48,925 --> 00:19:50,325
Are you Joseonjok?

264
00:19:51,365 --> 00:19:53,095
You speak Korean very well.

265
00:19:55,065 --> 00:19:57,165
What are you talking about? I'm not Joseonjok.

266
00:20:02,245 --> 00:20:04,175
Anyway, thank you.

267
00:20:07,315 --> 00:20:10,314
Gosh, turning away paying customers.

268
00:20:10,315 --> 00:20:12,285
He may be my own son,

269
00:20:12,585 --> 00:20:15,955
but he's just pathetic. Unbelievable.

270
00:20:17,425 --> 00:20:19,525
I'm so dumbfounded that I'm speechless!

271
00:20:20,595 --> 00:20:23,825
A waddling fat pig who can't even run tries to escape?

272
00:20:23,895 --> 00:20:26,995
Sir, I'm sorry. You two were in the middle of an important talk.

273
00:20:28,735 --> 00:20:31,705
- I'll lose weight and stop running. - Darn.

274
00:20:31,905 --> 00:20:34,645
Okay, I'll take my punishment.

275
00:20:35,775 --> 00:20:39,845
But can you please do it somewhere else? I really hate this place.

276
00:20:40,145 --> 00:20:42,115
I'll take twice the beating, please.

277
00:20:42,545 --> 00:20:45,115
- Please, sir? - Shut it.

278
00:20:55,895 --> 00:20:56,965
And what is that?

279
00:20:58,165 --> 00:21:01,335
- Do women come here too? - That's not a woman. He's a man.

280
00:21:04,875 --> 00:21:07,505
(Reflection)

281
00:21:07,705 --> 00:21:08,705
You.

282
00:21:10,005 --> 00:21:11,075
Turn around.

283
00:21:17,345 --> 00:21:18,455
What are you in for?

284
00:21:19,655 --> 00:21:22,955
That punk's in for trying to rape Ms. Jang from the butcher shop.

285
00:21:23,455 --> 00:21:26,195
They say he's freakishly strong. If he grabs you, it's all night.

286
00:21:27,155 --> 00:21:31,025
I'm too nervous. Can't he just go do his reflecting somewhere else?

287
00:21:32,565 --> 00:21:33,735
He's scaring me.

288
00:21:35,035 --> 00:21:36,065
All of you, get out.

289
00:21:37,235 --> 00:21:38,405
Didn't you hear me?

290
00:21:41,445 --> 00:21:45,345
Your reflection time is over. Get back to your day jobs!

291
00:21:47,045 --> 00:21:48,745
- Thank you, sir. - Thank you, sir.

292
00:21:48,885 --> 00:21:50,245
- Thank you, sir. - You.

293
00:21:54,555 --> 00:21:55,555
You.

294
00:21:57,425 --> 00:21:59,695
You stay. I've got a job for you.

295
00:22:01,795 --> 00:22:05,765
- What's the job? - Teach this punk a lesson.

296
00:22:07,065 --> 00:22:09,205
Just do what you do best.

297
00:22:13,605 --> 00:22:16,645
No way. What if someone walks in on us?

298
00:22:17,075 --> 00:22:19,974
- It's embarrassing. - I'll lock the door from outside.

299
00:22:19,975 --> 00:22:21,075
Don't worry.

300
00:22:23,045 --> 00:22:25,615
So, how much time do I get?

301
00:22:26,085 --> 00:22:29,025
- You can take all night, can't you? - What?

302
00:22:29,985 --> 00:22:31,055
Thank you.

303
00:22:32,095 --> 00:22:35,825
- Thank you. - Wait, what are you talking about?

304
00:22:35,895 --> 00:22:39,635
This little punk... I'll make a new man out of him.

305
00:22:42,705 --> 00:22:46,175
(Reflection)

306
00:23:01,155 --> 00:23:02,855
Wang Gi Cheol, that scum!

307
00:23:15,135 --> 00:23:16,935
(Wang Gi Cheol)

308
00:23:17,005 --> 00:23:18,365
(Using them to find Chairman Choi)

309
00:23:18,475 --> 00:23:20,395
(You're only alive for my revenge. Don't forget)

310
00:23:24,815 --> 00:23:29,745
The Mono Group heir's fiance cheated with her friend. She's livid.

311
00:23:30,485 --> 00:23:31,555
How humiliating is that?

312
00:23:32,785 --> 00:23:36,155
But is that worth all that money?

313
00:23:37,055 --> 00:23:38,455
The motive's too weak.

314
00:23:39,655 --> 00:23:43,625
Just like Myo Jin said, there must be a much bigger reason.

315
00:23:44,025 --> 00:23:46,665
(Ham Myo Jin)

316
00:23:48,535 --> 00:23:49,565
Hey, Myo Jin.

317
00:23:49,835 --> 00:23:51,035
We were wrong.

318
00:23:51,505 --> 00:23:53,704
- We've been looking at this wrong. - Wrong about what?

319
00:23:53,705 --> 00:23:56,245
From the very beginning, Lee Jong Su never cared for Hee Soo.

320
00:23:57,045 --> 00:23:59,291
He was harassing Hee Soo to get to Chairman Choi Young Ho.

321
00:23:59,315 --> 00:24:01,284
He wanted to meet Chairman Choi? Why?

322
00:24:01,285 --> 00:24:05,915
Lee Jong Su texted Wang Gi Cheol, and they were talking about money.

323
00:24:05,985 --> 00:24:07,831
He said he needed to meet Chairman Choi Young Ho.

324
00:24:07,855 --> 00:24:11,795
That's it. He'll expose his daughter's secrets.

325
00:24:11,925 --> 00:24:14,525
What parent would stand for that? He could name his price!

326
00:24:14,595 --> 00:24:16,165
But that's not all.

327
00:24:16,925 --> 00:24:18,535
There's something else that's strange.

328
00:24:18,795 --> 00:24:22,265
Lee Jong Su keeps mentioning my name to this guy, Wang Gi Cheol.

329
00:24:22,335 --> 00:24:25,735
Like he knows me. Do you know a Wang Gi Cheol?

330
00:24:25,905 --> 00:24:27,775
Wang Gi Cheol? No.

331
00:24:28,175 --> 00:24:30,505
Doesn't ring a bell. What are they talking about?

332
00:24:30,675 --> 00:24:34,015
They mention me and Chairman Choi. It's all about money.

333
00:24:36,745 --> 00:24:38,731
As if I have some relationship with Chairman Choi.

334
00:24:38,755 --> 00:24:41,454
This is driving me crazy. This won't do.

335
00:24:41,455 --> 00:24:44,955
Tomorrow, we make Lee Jong Su talk, one way or another!

336
00:24:46,855 --> 00:24:47,995
I'll call you back.

337
00:24:56,405 --> 00:24:57,664
(Wang Gi Cheol)

338
00:24:57,665 --> 00:24:59,111
(Looks like Choi Young Ho's daughter will come back soon.)

339
00:24:59,135 --> 00:25:00,251
(Meet in front of Chungwoon Store at 6pm.)

340
00:25:00,275 --> 00:25:02,035
(Her name is Choi Hee Soo. She's an artist.)

341
00:25:05,145 --> 00:25:07,775
You vicious wench... Wasn't killing those two...

342
00:25:08,445 --> 00:25:09,845
enough?

343
00:25:11,955 --> 00:25:13,315
You can just stop now.

344
00:25:14,185 --> 00:25:15,585
This revenge of yours.

345
00:25:30,805 --> 00:25:33,075
The design competition judges have been announced.

346
00:25:33,805 --> 00:25:36,605
Oh Sang Il is the head of the jury.

347
00:25:37,775 --> 00:25:41,175
The competition's eligibility rules have been changed as well.

348
00:25:41,945 --> 00:25:44,261
They've removed the requirements for industry experience and awards.

349
00:25:44,285 --> 00:25:48,925
They'll focus only on abilities relevant to this competition.

350
00:25:52,655 --> 00:25:54,595
What modern architects need...

351
00:25:54,655 --> 00:25:58,065
for the very essence of the works they create...

352
00:25:58,195 --> 00:26:01,865
- is silence. - And when do you think...

353
00:26:02,665 --> 00:26:06,775
is the right time for architects to break that silence?

354
00:26:06,835 --> 00:26:10,005
I believe the silence must continue. But...

355
00:26:10,705 --> 00:26:12,674
through communion,

356
00:26:12,675 --> 00:26:14,791
communication between the structure and its people...

357
00:26:14,815 --> 00:26:18,055
can it finally break free from that silence.

358
00:26:21,885 --> 00:26:24,795
There is a common misconception.

359
00:26:25,725 --> 00:26:27,255
With any building,

360
00:26:28,195 --> 00:26:32,295
people only see form and function, but the philosophy, soul within...

361
00:26:32,365 --> 00:26:34,465
are disappearing without them even noticing.

362
00:26:35,065 --> 00:26:37,635
As for you, Jun Ho, where are you headed?

363
00:26:38,775 --> 00:26:40,205
Can you tell me?

364
00:26:41,405 --> 00:26:43,845
"There is no such thing as architecture."

365
00:26:44,845 --> 00:26:46,415
"There are only architects."

366
00:26:47,215 --> 00:26:48,485
It's a saying...

367
00:26:48,885 --> 00:26:51,185
that I always reflect upon in my work.

368
00:26:52,185 --> 00:26:53,685
It's become my personal motto.

369
00:26:56,325 --> 00:26:59,325
It seems Oh Sang Il himself asked the Culture Ministry...

370
00:26:59,525 --> 00:27:01,725
to change the competition's rules.

371
00:27:04,225 --> 00:27:05,235
That's great.

372
00:27:07,835 --> 00:27:09,805
Two hundred grand? In cash?

373
00:27:10,265 --> 00:27:13,375
- Right now? - Keep it down. Someone will hear.

374
00:27:13,975 --> 00:27:15,615
What, you want a microphone or something?

375
00:27:16,005 --> 00:27:18,214
But if I bring her and you flake, I swear...

376
00:27:18,215 --> 00:27:21,985
Man, I told you. They're my right and left hands.

377
00:27:23,085 --> 00:27:24,415
Two hundred grand...

378
00:27:25,255 --> 00:27:26,855
You said she's got a pretty face, right?

379
00:27:27,315 --> 00:27:29,885
- And a great body. - I can guarantee that much.

380
00:27:31,085 --> 00:27:34,325
She's the "Who am I?" type. A total train wreck every day.

381
00:27:34,625 --> 00:27:36,001
What? What are you even talking about?

382
00:27:36,025 --> 00:27:38,865
I'm saying she's philosophical.

383
00:27:39,135 --> 00:27:40,895
She's tall and sexy.

384
00:27:44,065 --> 00:27:45,075
Okay.

385
00:27:47,835 --> 00:27:50,675
Why is he just sleeping? Is he even sorry?

386
00:27:50,705 --> 00:27:53,975
He's been through something. It must've been rough on him.

387
00:27:56,815 --> 00:27:58,385
Looks like he's lost some weight.

388
00:27:59,485 --> 00:28:00,555
Didn't you feed him?

389
00:28:00,685 --> 00:28:04,055
He was being "educated" all night, without food or sleep.

390
00:28:05,755 --> 00:28:07,495
So what are you going to do?

391
00:28:07,855 --> 00:28:11,395
- Haven't you worked with me before? - Right. Got it.

392
00:28:18,035 --> 00:28:19,205
Ex...

393
00:28:20,435 --> 00:28:21,435
Excuse me?

394
00:28:22,375 --> 00:28:25,615
Sorry to bother you while you two are talking,

395
00:28:26,245 --> 00:28:27,845
but there's something I need to say.

396
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:29,885
I'd rather just die.

397
00:28:31,855 --> 00:28:33,755
I can't live like this anymore.

398
00:28:34,255 --> 00:28:36,655
What, you want me to kill you?

399
00:28:38,895 --> 00:28:40,015
No, that's not what I meant.

400
00:28:40,255 --> 00:28:43,365
The truth is, I have a ton of money.

401
00:28:44,295 --> 00:28:45,295
How about we settle this?

402
00:28:45,795 --> 00:28:46,995
I mean, at this point,

403
00:28:48,265 --> 00:28:50,005
I've been through enough, don't you think?

404
00:28:51,365 --> 00:28:54,075
Why offer me money? You rich or something?

405
00:28:57,575 --> 00:29:00,015
I'll give you whatever you want. I won't haggle one bit.

406
00:29:00,115 --> 00:29:02,845
In fact, since we're on the subject, I'll wire it to you right now.

407
00:29:02,985 --> 00:29:04,245
No fuss. How about it?

408
00:29:07,755 --> 00:29:08,755
Hey, you.

409
00:29:10,025 --> 00:29:13,155
Do you have any idea who the people you scammed and beat up are?

410
00:29:14,355 --> 00:29:16,964
That was his one and only brother and his colleagues.

411
00:29:16,965 --> 00:29:19,335
Money won't solve this, you idiot!

412
00:29:19,665 --> 00:29:21,035
Darn...

413
00:29:25,305 --> 00:29:27,205
(An Woo Sik, El Karaoke Bar)

414
00:29:32,845 --> 00:29:33,945
He's actually calling.

415
00:29:35,485 --> 00:29:36,615
Is the trace ready?

416
00:29:36,915 --> 00:29:41,115
His location will pop up. But the call must last for a minute.

417
00:29:41,455 --> 00:29:43,361
You pull any funny business, and you're dead where you stand.

418
00:29:43,385 --> 00:29:46,794
- Of course not! Absolutely not! - One minute.

419
00:29:46,795 --> 00:29:48,265
One minute?

420
00:29:52,565 --> 00:29:53,635
Okay.

421
00:29:57,505 --> 00:29:58,505
Hello?

422
00:29:59,835 --> 00:30:01,621
Am I speaking to the man who's too busy to answer his phone?

423
00:30:01,645 --> 00:30:03,285
What, are you my girlfriend or something?

424
00:30:03,505 --> 00:30:05,215
Why do you keep blowing up my phone?

425
00:30:05,275 --> 00:30:07,115
Business must be booming for you.

426
00:30:07,375 --> 00:30:09,661
So I guess my business isn't worth your time now, is that it?

427
00:30:09,685 --> 00:30:14,085
Of course not. What's up? You sound like you've got good news.

428
00:30:14,155 --> 00:30:16,285
I've got a group, but the headcount is a little high.

429
00:30:16,625 --> 00:30:17,625
How many?

430
00:30:20,725 --> 00:30:22,995
- Three. - What? Three people?

431
00:30:24,925 --> 00:30:27,895
I'm kidding. It's 30.

432
00:30:27,965 --> 00:30:29,065
Now that's a jackpot.

433
00:30:29,135 --> 00:30:30,781
Too many for you to handle, though, right?

434
00:30:30,805 --> 00:30:33,875
I mean, the biggest so far was, what, 12 people, wasn't it?

435
00:30:33,935 --> 00:30:36,575
Plus, they're a bunch of idiots, so they're ripe for the picking.

436
00:30:38,075 --> 00:30:41,685
So, what? You want my help? It's too good to pass up, isn't it?

437
00:30:41,745 --> 00:30:43,284
Two grand a head, plus extra fees.

438
00:30:43,285 --> 00:30:44,785
Think how much that all adds up to.

439
00:30:44,845 --> 00:30:46,285
It's a total gold mine, right?

440
00:30:46,755 --> 00:30:49,655
- When is it? - The day after tomorrow, 8pm.

441
00:30:49,825 --> 00:30:52,695
Darn, that won't work. I have to finish something that day.

442
00:30:53,295 --> 00:30:54,354
Call me for the next one. I'm hanging up.

443
00:30:54,355 --> 00:30:57,125
Wait! Hang on. What about next week?

444
00:30:57,195 --> 00:30:59,435
There's this important gathering. It's about 50 people.

445
00:30:59,495 --> 00:31:02,305
It's a total cakewalk. But hold on. What was the date again? Hang on.

446
00:31:02,365 --> 00:31:04,081
What are you talking about? I'm hanging up. I'm busy.

447
00:31:04,105 --> 00:31:06,405
Hey, you scum! When I tell you to do it, you do it!

448
00:31:06,475 --> 00:31:10,605
Work? What work? Darn. Please, don't hang up.

449
00:31:12,315 --> 00:31:13,375
Psycho.

450
00:31:14,515 --> 00:31:16,445
Boss, I've got him.

451
00:31:20,315 --> 00:31:21,355
Have a drink.

452
00:31:23,885 --> 00:31:24,885
Yes.

453
00:31:43,605 --> 00:31:45,075
You're right, CEO Ryu.

454
00:31:45,615 --> 00:31:48,375
And it's true we achieved our goals within the agreed-upon time frame.

455
00:31:48,815 --> 00:31:50,895
And your request to separate from the head office...

456
00:31:51,145 --> 00:31:52,915
is, in my opinion, justified.

457
00:31:53,985 --> 00:31:55,485
The Vice Chairman, however,

458
00:31:55,985 --> 00:31:59,625
says the one with the biggest issue with our company separating...

459
00:32:00,255 --> 00:32:04,165
- is you, head of the legal team. - Yes, that is correct.

460
00:32:04,325 --> 00:32:05,495
And why is that?

461
00:32:05,635 --> 00:32:09,505
Due to the Mono Group's Articles, Article 19, Clause 3.

462
00:32:10,265 --> 00:32:14,135
It states that in a force majeure, the company's decisions...

463
00:32:14,405 --> 00:32:17,405
are to be made by the chief executive.

464
00:32:18,145 --> 00:32:22,045
As you know, the Vice Chairman is filling that position temporarily.

465
00:32:22,515 --> 00:32:26,715
We can't move forward on a matter that the Vice Chairman opposes.

466
00:32:30,325 --> 00:32:33,155
Article 5, Clause 1 of the Board of Directors' Operating Regulations.

467
00:32:33,225 --> 00:32:37,695
If the CEO becomes incapacitated, the Board has 60 days...

468
00:32:37,765 --> 00:32:40,035
to elect a new replacement.

469
00:32:40,335 --> 00:32:43,535
But the deadline in that article has already passed.

470
00:32:44,965 --> 00:32:48,445
It's not difficult to convene the board,

471
00:32:48,575 --> 00:32:51,175
but it's taking time to ensure a careful selection,

472
00:32:51,245 --> 00:32:53,875
so it would be a stretch to call it illegal.

473
00:32:54,215 --> 00:32:56,715
I'm sorry, but I must ask you to wait a little longer.

474
00:32:56,785 --> 00:33:00,155
It seems there's another reason, one you're not telling me.

475
00:33:21,505 --> 00:33:25,645
May I speak frankly?

476
00:33:26,245 --> 00:33:28,914
- By all means. - CEO Ryu, we're out of options.

477
00:33:28,915 --> 00:33:30,715
Let's just proceed with a lawsuit.

478
00:33:32,015 --> 00:33:34,175
There's no reasoning with the Vice Chairman right now.

479
00:33:34,615 --> 00:33:38,185
I said to get board approval first, but he's turned a deaf ear.

480
00:33:39,495 --> 00:33:42,565
I told him that if you make a move, he'll have to accept your demands.

481
00:33:42,625 --> 00:33:46,335
- But no matter how hard I tried... - You've worked hard, team leader.

482
00:33:49,105 --> 00:33:53,135
Conflicts come down to emotions, don't they? Not logic.

483
00:33:53,475 --> 00:33:55,975
The Vice Chairman isn't going to change.

484
00:33:57,675 --> 00:33:59,375
I did everything I could,

485
00:34:00,275 --> 00:34:01,415
but it wasn't enough.

486
00:34:04,215 --> 00:34:07,855
I appreciate your proposal. Let's leave it at that for today.

487
00:34:08,525 --> 00:34:10,085
Of course. Yes.

488
00:34:12,325 --> 00:34:13,555
Understood.

489
00:34:18,665 --> 00:34:19,835
Just look straight ahead.

490
00:34:20,465 --> 00:34:22,105
He was trying to bait you into a lawsuit.

491
00:34:22,305 --> 00:34:25,975
He'll drag this to the Supreme Court to expose a side of you...

492
00:34:26,035 --> 00:34:27,805
that the public knows nothing about.

493
00:34:28,235 --> 00:34:31,975
- He'll keep provoking you, CEO. - Is this who Manager Kim mentioned?

494
00:34:32,045 --> 00:34:33,274
Yesterday, he called the head of the legal team...

495
00:34:33,275 --> 00:34:34,675
and gave him some kind of order.

496
00:34:36,245 --> 00:34:39,985
Since he despises me, I'll just have to give him what he wants.

497
00:34:40,785 --> 00:34:44,085
A close friend asked me for a favour, and I feel like I let you down.

498
00:34:44,255 --> 00:34:46,955
No, you did more than enough. Thank you.

499
00:34:47,325 --> 00:34:49,401
You should also check your online accounts frequently.

500
00:34:49,425 --> 00:34:51,271
There's someone in IT who's a junior of the legal team's head.

501
00:34:51,295 --> 00:34:53,975
A real weirdo who gets a kick out of cracking impossible passwords.

502
00:35:01,805 --> 00:35:05,915
You resisted, saying nothing's left to bleed you for?

503
00:35:05,975 --> 00:35:09,115
- What nerve, you jerk! - Okay, I get it!

504
00:35:09,385 --> 00:35:11,685
I get it, so please, just stop.

505
00:35:11,745 --> 00:35:15,485
You get it now? Why now? Why not before I got here?

506
00:35:15,555 --> 00:35:19,425
Things would've been so much easier if you'd figured it out sooner.

507
00:35:19,525 --> 00:35:23,095
- I'll be out first thing tomorrow! - Get out!

508
00:35:23,165 --> 00:35:24,495
- Why? - I said, get out!

509
00:35:26,635 --> 00:35:29,265
No. Where do you think you're going?

510
00:35:29,365 --> 00:35:32,305
Everyone, stay right where you are. Got it?

511
00:35:32,535 --> 00:35:35,105
I'm putting a stop to this demolition today!

512
00:35:35,475 --> 00:35:38,075
You'll have to see my face every single day.

513
00:35:38,675 --> 00:35:40,615
Hey, how great is that?

514
00:35:40,675 --> 00:35:43,815
Look at this huge crowd here.

515
00:35:45,455 --> 00:35:49,585
Just keep doing business here forever.

516
00:35:50,285 --> 00:35:51,585
On and on and on.

517
00:35:55,125 --> 00:35:56,965
You young punks...

518
00:35:57,625 --> 00:35:59,595
What's all this chaos in the middle of the day?

519
00:36:01,535 --> 00:36:05,265
Well, look what the cat dragged in. Been a while, hasn't it?

520
00:36:07,505 --> 00:36:09,845
Wait. Gi Cheol.

521
00:36:10,505 --> 00:36:13,175
(Merchants to be compensated with realistic value for property)

522
00:36:17,085 --> 00:36:20,185
Hey, I heard you'd made some bank,

523
00:36:21,055 --> 00:36:23,815
but I didn't think I'd find you here holding out for a bigger payout.

524
00:36:23,955 --> 00:36:25,725
Holding out? Don't be ridiculous.

525
00:36:26,055 --> 00:36:28,665
Come on. The offer must be pretty darn good.

526
00:36:29,125 --> 00:36:31,065
Must be nice for you, making all that money.

527
00:36:32,135 --> 00:36:34,165
Stop harassing these people and leave them alone.

528
00:36:34,995 --> 00:36:36,705
They're all leaving next week anyway.

529
00:36:36,765 --> 00:36:40,005
What? That soon? No, that won't work.

530
00:36:40,135 --> 00:36:43,105
Hey, tell them to hold out for just a few more days.

531
00:36:44,105 --> 00:36:46,675
Do you know what my day rate is? We can't wrap this up so soon.

532
00:36:47,345 --> 00:36:49,985
Darn, these guys are such cowards.

533
00:36:51,445 --> 00:36:52,455
You're insane.

534
00:36:53,215 --> 00:36:55,315
I'm just strapped for cash.

535
00:36:55,885 --> 00:36:57,645
Let's just string this along for a few days.

536
00:36:57,825 --> 00:36:59,425
Around ten days?

537
00:36:59,925 --> 00:37:01,425
Don't be ridiculous.

538
00:37:02,125 --> 00:37:04,465
- Don't come back here again. - Come on.

539
00:37:05,465 --> 00:37:07,335
We're all just trying to make a living.

540
00:37:07,695 --> 00:37:09,735
We should help each other out when times are tough.

541
00:37:10,435 --> 00:37:12,375
Your brilliant prison buddy.

542
00:37:13,105 --> 00:37:14,275
Brother!

543
00:37:15,275 --> 00:37:16,375
Darn it.

544
00:37:18,275 --> 00:37:19,575
Gosh, Detective Woo.

545
00:37:21,275 --> 00:37:22,315
You punk.

546
00:37:24,945 --> 00:37:29,255
Are we shooting a spy movie here? What is all this?

547
00:37:30,555 --> 00:37:31,625
It's complicated.

548
00:37:31,955 --> 00:37:33,695
- How have you been? - I'm good.

549
00:37:34,055 --> 00:37:36,995
We could've just met at the station. Why won't you come inside?

550
00:37:37,595 --> 00:37:39,395
What, did you commit a crime or something?

551
00:37:40,295 --> 00:37:42,235
Too many prying ears at the station.

552
00:37:43,335 --> 00:37:46,505
If I see someone I know, it's all, "Who's visiting?" "Why is he here?"

553
00:37:47,075 --> 00:37:49,075
And I can't be bothered with the pointless gossip.

554
00:37:49,275 --> 00:37:51,305
Okay, I get it. So just spit it out already.

555
00:37:51,605 --> 00:37:53,475
What's with all the suspense?

556
00:37:53,845 --> 00:37:55,444
If this is nothing important,

557
00:37:55,445 --> 00:37:57,125
let's go have hangover soup with kkakdugi.

558
00:37:58,415 --> 00:37:59,655
You're buying lunch.

559
00:38:00,585 --> 00:38:01,785
All right, kid, I'll buy.

560
00:38:03,455 --> 00:38:04,535
But listen, Detective Gang,

561
00:38:05,285 --> 00:38:08,355
your team was in charge of the Jebu Island villa explosion case, right?

562
00:38:09,265 --> 00:38:10,825
I've taken over that case now.

563
00:38:11,095 --> 00:38:12,575
My chief brought it over to our team.

564
00:38:14,065 --> 00:38:15,065
Sir.

565
00:38:15,935 --> 00:38:17,735
If I'd known you were going to bring that up,

566
00:38:17,835 --> 00:38:19,205
I wouldn't have shown up.

567
00:38:20,505 --> 00:38:22,775
Come on, don't be like that. Just talk to me, punk.

568
00:38:23,275 --> 00:38:27,175
I can't speak for the others, but you don't cut corners.

569
00:38:29,545 --> 00:38:30,745
So what happened this time?

570
00:38:31,845 --> 00:38:34,525
I heard Chief Son put in his papers because of his chronic illness.

571
00:38:35,115 --> 00:38:38,585
You should've closed the case first before you transferred.

572
00:38:38,955 --> 00:38:40,755
What was the big rush to transfer here?

573
00:38:42,725 --> 00:38:44,765
You're hiding something, aren't you?

574
00:38:45,225 --> 00:38:47,165
That's all complete nonsense.

575
00:38:48,965 --> 00:38:49,965
What?

576
00:38:51,435 --> 00:38:53,305
You know what our chief is like, right?

577
00:38:53,835 --> 00:38:55,745
When he's on a case, he's sharp as a knife.

578
00:38:56,145 --> 00:39:00,415
I admired him. That's why I chose to stay with him over other offers.

579
00:39:00,975 --> 00:39:02,415
But that's not who he was.

580
00:39:03,045 --> 00:39:05,415
I completely misjudged the man.

581
00:39:05,785 --> 00:39:08,115
Or something made him do a complete 180.

582
00:39:16,395 --> 00:39:18,715
It was like watching Cinderella at the stroke of midnight.

583
00:39:18,865 --> 00:39:21,235
He just vanishes every chance he gets.

584
00:39:21,695 --> 00:39:24,505
Gosh, whatever he was doing, he took his sweet time.

585
00:39:25,205 --> 00:39:26,835
Then it just hit me.

586
00:39:37,345 --> 00:39:38,345
Detective Gang.

587
00:39:40,685 --> 00:39:41,915
The chief quit.

588
00:39:42,625 --> 00:39:44,755
- What? - You didn't know?

589
00:39:47,695 --> 00:39:48,695
And wouldn't you know it?

590
00:39:49,425 --> 00:39:51,864
He tells me how many times a day he uses the bathroom,

591
00:39:51,865 --> 00:39:53,535
and he just leaves without a single word.

592
00:39:53,895 --> 00:39:56,765
And no one heard anything about him being sick enough to go on leave.

593
00:39:57,165 --> 00:39:58,335
What on earth is that?

594
00:39:58,975 --> 00:40:02,745
So I got so fed up. I just up and quit too.

595
00:40:03,475 --> 00:40:05,775
Did you, by any chance, tell anyone...

596
00:40:06,075 --> 00:40:08,075
No. Did you report it to the higher-ups?

597
00:40:08,815 --> 00:40:09,885
Come on.

598
00:40:10,515 --> 00:40:12,655
You know darn well I could never do that, so why ask?

599
00:40:15,755 --> 00:40:16,755
Look.

600
00:40:17,755 --> 00:40:20,495
There's not a single piece of evidence left in this case.

601
00:40:21,255 --> 00:40:25,465
- And this isn't an arson case. - What do you mean it's not?

602
00:40:25,495 --> 00:40:29,365
We found what's presumed to be the murder weapon at the scene,

603
00:40:29,465 --> 00:40:31,385
and it's currently undergoing forensic analysis.

604
00:40:32,775 --> 00:40:34,175
Which means it's a murder case.

605
00:40:38,445 --> 00:40:40,715
That's the only piece of evidence we were able to find.

606
00:40:41,345 --> 00:40:42,345
There's nothing else.

607
00:40:43,845 --> 00:40:47,115
Did you find anything in the initial investigation?

608
00:40:47,455 --> 00:40:49,225
Or maybe something that comes to mind?

609
00:40:49,485 --> 00:40:51,855
How would I know? I'm the guy who quit.

610
00:40:52,085 --> 00:40:54,355
You'd be better off asking Chief Son.

611
00:40:54,625 --> 00:40:57,365
Not that he'll tell you, even if he knows something.

612
00:40:57,425 --> 00:40:58,725
Come on, don't be like that.

613
00:40:59,365 --> 00:41:02,565
Do you think I'd come all this way if I wasn't desperate?

614
00:41:03,735 --> 00:41:05,205
Trust me, I was surprised too.

615
00:41:05,775 --> 00:41:10,475
I figured you wouldn't have noticed even if I'd dropped dead.

616
00:41:12,675 --> 00:41:14,845
Hey, are you really going to be like this?

617
00:41:15,745 --> 00:41:20,015
Who lent you cash last year when you were bouncing between rentals?

618
00:41:20,115 --> 00:41:21,515
Interest-free, I might add.

619
00:41:21,585 --> 00:41:23,985
That's a low blow. Fine, I'll pay you back.

620
00:41:24,155 --> 00:41:26,955
So what have you been up to? Why show up now all of a sudden?

621
00:41:27,025 --> 00:41:29,185
We may be on different teams, but if you cared at all,

622
00:41:29,365 --> 00:41:31,871
how could you not have known how much I was struggling with this?

623
00:41:31,895 --> 00:41:33,135
What, are you dating someone?

624
00:41:33,995 --> 00:41:34,995
What?

625
00:41:36,365 --> 00:41:38,205
You know very well I'm not an idiot.

626
00:41:38,705 --> 00:41:40,705
And you have the nerve to ask me about it now.

627
00:41:42,005 --> 00:41:44,105
Detective Gang, did you...

628
00:41:45,305 --> 00:41:47,745
The hard drive with the CCTV footage from the villa...

629
00:41:48,915 --> 00:41:50,385
It wasn't destroyed in the fire.

630
00:41:51,245 --> 00:41:52,555
Someone took it beforehand.

631
00:41:54,155 --> 00:41:55,655
Took it? Who?

632
00:41:56,425 --> 00:41:58,585
What are we going to do with you?

633
00:41:59,325 --> 00:42:00,825
You've really lost your touch.

634
00:42:02,665 --> 00:42:05,325
Of the four so-called big shots, two of them are dead.

635
00:42:06,295 --> 00:42:07,595
That leaves two, doesn't it?

636
00:42:08,565 --> 00:42:10,605
Do I need to draw you a picture?

637
00:42:13,005 --> 00:42:14,135
It's obvious.

638
00:42:17,875 --> 00:42:19,645
(Wang Gi Cheol)

639
00:42:55,175 --> 00:42:56,245
Hello?

640
00:43:01,255 --> 00:43:03,025
My name is Ham Myo Jin.

641
00:43:06,355 --> 00:43:07,355
Hello?

642
00:43:14,235 --> 00:43:15,365
How have you been?

643
00:43:16,535 --> 00:43:17,535
I'm sorry?

644
00:43:18,065 --> 00:43:19,605
I heard about your accident,

645
00:43:21,335 --> 00:43:22,415
so I was worried about you.

646
00:43:22,905 --> 00:43:25,815
Do you know me well?

647
00:43:27,475 --> 00:43:30,415
I lost my memory from the shock of the accident.

648
00:43:31,315 --> 00:43:33,955
I'm recovering, but I still can't remember much.

649
00:43:34,985 --> 00:43:37,225
Then how did you know to call me?

650
00:43:37,585 --> 00:43:39,455
I just found the phone I'd lost,

651
00:43:39,855 --> 00:43:41,775
and I'm calling because I saw your text message.

652
00:43:42,425 --> 00:43:45,225
It seemed we talked a lot, so I was hoping you could help me.

653
00:43:45,865 --> 00:43:46,865
Interesting.

654
00:43:47,665 --> 00:43:50,105
So you're saying you're back to square one?

655
00:43:50,935 --> 00:43:51,935
What do you mean?

656
00:43:52,235 --> 00:43:53,535
It means you don't remember...

657
00:43:54,905 --> 00:43:56,945
who I am now, right?

658
00:44:00,575 --> 00:44:01,645
Please, just tell me.

659
00:44:02,345 --> 00:44:03,845
How do I know you?

660
00:44:05,415 --> 00:44:06,755
You don't need to know.

661
00:44:07,855 --> 00:44:09,485
It's dangerous for both of us if you do.

662
00:44:09,785 --> 00:44:12,425
Hang up and delete my number.

663
00:44:12,925 --> 00:44:14,655
Not that I'll be picking up again anyway.

664
00:44:14,725 --> 00:44:15,995
I met Lee Jong Su.

665
00:44:16,965 --> 00:44:18,325
He got into an accident.

666
00:44:19,265 --> 00:44:20,505
He's in the hospital right now.

667
00:44:23,705 --> 00:44:24,735
Hello?

668
00:44:25,535 --> 00:44:26,535
Who did it?

669
00:44:27,535 --> 00:44:30,375
- What? - Who did that to him?

670
00:44:31,805 --> 00:44:34,675
Don't tell me... Was it you?

671
00:44:36,785 --> 00:44:38,085
I'll tell you in person.

672
00:44:39,115 --> 00:44:40,115
Everything.

673
00:44:42,525 --> 00:44:47,525
(We oppose this outrageous construction.)

674
00:45:12,015 --> 00:45:16,325
(Star Karaoke Bar)

675
00:45:58,895 --> 00:46:00,135
Why are you back here?

676
00:46:08,475 --> 00:46:10,375
Go on, try me, you jerk!

677
00:46:12,145 --> 00:46:15,275
I warned you. Nothing good can come of us meeting.

678
00:46:15,945 --> 00:46:16,945
You're wrong.

679
00:46:17,945 --> 00:46:19,585
I want to get my memories back.

680
00:46:20,215 --> 00:46:21,415
That's why I'm here.

681
00:46:21,815 --> 00:46:23,485
What happened to Jong Su?

682
00:46:23,625 --> 00:46:26,895
I heard he'd threatened my friend, so I went to see him.

683
00:46:27,325 --> 00:46:28,995
To ask him what was going on.

684
00:46:38,965 --> 00:46:40,435
But Choi Hee Soo is dead.

685
00:46:41,875 --> 00:46:44,675
You know Hee Soo? How do you know her?

686
00:46:45,305 --> 00:46:48,075
- What was she to you? - Since I hadn't heard from you,

687
00:46:50,415 --> 00:46:54,185
- I thought this was all behind you. - Please, I'm begging you.

688
00:46:54,955 --> 00:46:56,955
Please, just tell me everything you know about me.

689
00:47:16,575 --> 00:47:19,745
What exactly...

690
00:47:20,645 --> 00:47:22,275
do you know right now?

691
00:47:24,785 --> 00:47:25,785
At first, I thought...

692
00:47:26,985 --> 00:47:28,455
I'd betrayed my friend...

693
00:47:29,885 --> 00:47:32,325
and was a piece of trash for stealing her boyfriend.

694
00:47:34,925 --> 00:47:36,825
But apparently, for some reason,

695
00:47:37,595 --> 00:47:40,635
that all happened while I was trying to meet Chairman Choi Young Ho.

696
00:47:42,835 --> 00:47:44,595
And you know what that reason is, don't you?

697
00:47:45,235 --> 00:47:46,535
I'm warning you.

698
00:47:47,105 --> 00:47:48,535
Forget everything and move on.

699
00:47:49,775 --> 00:47:51,645
It's for your own good.

700
00:47:52,875 --> 00:47:55,175
No, I need to know.

701
00:47:55,975 --> 00:47:58,185
Why I stole my friend's boyfriend.

702
00:47:58,645 --> 00:48:01,085
Why I tried to see Chairman Choi, a man I've never even seen.

703
00:48:01,585 --> 00:48:03,985
You're starting to sound like your old self.

704
00:48:06,495 --> 00:48:09,155
That spitfire who came at me with a knife,

705
00:48:09,925 --> 00:48:11,695
swearing you were going to kill me.

706
00:48:12,265 --> 00:48:13,335
I did that...

707
00:48:14,795 --> 00:48:16,065
to you?

708
00:48:47,065 --> 00:48:48,865
You were in the ninth grade.

709
00:48:49,705 --> 00:48:53,535
Your parents were always happy and smiling...

710
00:48:55,175 --> 00:48:56,675
and were devout in their faith.

711
00:49:02,745 --> 00:49:04,485
The church my mom and dad...

712
00:49:05,685 --> 00:49:06,685
used to go to?

713
00:49:11,185 --> 00:49:14,695
That's when everything started to fall apart.

714
00:49:25,565 --> 00:49:26,775
There was an accident.

715
00:49:29,205 --> 00:49:30,475
Your family of three.

716
00:49:31,345 --> 00:49:33,275
Your father grew flowers for a living,

717
00:49:34,575 --> 00:49:36,145
so you all lived in a greenhouse.

718
00:49:38,245 --> 00:49:40,055
(Cheongham Farm)

719
00:49:42,185 --> 00:49:44,745
On the day a fire broke out and burned everything to the ground,

720
00:49:45,485 --> 00:49:46,795
your parents died,

721
00:49:49,395 --> 00:49:51,315
and you were the only one who made it out alive.

722
00:49:51,695 --> 00:49:53,395
What did you just say?

723
00:49:54,865 --> 00:49:58,365
Everyone in town thought I was just some jobless punk,

724
00:50:00,275 --> 00:50:01,505
and they couldn't stand me,

725
00:50:02,705 --> 00:50:05,145
but your parents were the only ones who were different.

726
00:50:05,945 --> 00:50:07,845
They treated me like a human being.

727
00:50:08,415 --> 00:50:10,415
- What does that have to do with it? - You were...

728
00:50:10,715 --> 00:50:12,315
always so bright and polite,

729
00:50:13,785 --> 00:50:15,885
a smart kid who did well in school.

730
00:50:17,255 --> 00:50:18,615
It was a real wake-up call for me.

731
00:50:20,525 --> 00:50:22,325
By the time I finally pulled myself together,

732
00:50:23,295 --> 00:50:25,795
- it was already too late. - What are you...

733
00:50:26,395 --> 00:50:28,665
- What are you talking about? - Just listen.

734
00:50:30,135 --> 00:50:31,495
I'm telling you this for a reason.

735
00:50:32,005 --> 00:50:34,475
(15 years ago)

736
00:50:34,535 --> 00:50:37,045
You'd kill such good people for money?

737
00:50:37,375 --> 00:50:41,015
- You scum! - They wouldn't have hurt a fly!

738
00:50:41,575 --> 00:50:44,375
Why did you kill them? Do you call yourself human? You piece of trash.

739
00:50:44,415 --> 00:50:47,985
Go to the fiery pit! You beast! Go to the fiery pit!

740
00:50:48,055 --> 00:50:50,455
Go to the fiery pit! For goodness' sake!

741
00:50:51,025 --> 00:50:52,125
Darn it!

742
00:50:52,725 --> 00:50:53,725
My gosh!

743
00:50:54,155 --> 00:50:56,595
- You evil jerk! - Just die!

744
00:50:56,665 --> 00:50:57,795
- You jerk! - You scum!

745
00:50:59,065 --> 00:51:00,165
Unbelievable!

746
00:51:00,965 --> 00:51:03,435
- Goodness! - Poor them.

747
00:51:04,535 --> 00:51:05,535
- Myo Jin! - Die!

748
00:51:07,175 --> 00:51:08,175
Die!

749
00:51:08,735 --> 00:51:09,745
Die!

750
00:51:10,645 --> 00:51:12,145
- No! - Don't!

751
00:51:12,205 --> 00:51:15,145
You die too! Let go! Let go of me!

752
00:51:15,245 --> 00:51:17,745
I'm going to kill you! I swear, I'm going to kill you!

753
00:51:18,015 --> 00:51:19,015
Hey!

754
00:51:22,185 --> 00:51:24,124
- Let go of me! - Get her in the car!

755
00:51:24,125 --> 00:51:27,255
Hey, where are you taking her?

756
00:51:27,325 --> 00:51:29,224
The suspect is injured, so we need to take her to the station.

757
00:51:29,225 --> 00:51:30,225
Move it, now!

758
00:51:30,226 --> 00:51:33,865
She lost her parents overnight. You think she's in her right mind?

759
00:51:34,065 --> 00:51:35,595
Have some pity. She's just a kid!

760
00:51:36,095 --> 00:51:39,135
Darn it! You call this justice? I can't just stand by.

761
00:51:39,335 --> 00:51:41,535
- No! Don't! - Hey, let me go! Let go!

762
00:51:41,605 --> 00:51:43,205
- Sir, we have to go! - But...

763
00:51:43,275 --> 00:51:44,945
- Let's go. - Gosh.

764
00:51:50,585 --> 00:51:53,585
- Come on. What is it? - Myo Jin, what's wrong?

765
00:51:54,255 --> 00:51:55,255
Oh, dear.

766
00:52:03,225 --> 00:52:04,525
Are you all right?

767
00:52:05,925 --> 00:52:06,935
Myo Jin.

768
00:52:32,855 --> 00:52:33,855
This...

769
00:52:34,895 --> 00:52:37,294
is the present you gave me that day.

770
00:52:37,295 --> 00:52:38,565
You're the one...

771
00:52:40,395 --> 00:52:42,265
who killed my mom and dad?

772
00:52:42,535 --> 00:52:44,905
And that's how I ended up in prison.

773
00:52:47,535 --> 00:52:51,475
I heard you were taken in by your parents' church.

774
00:52:52,245 --> 00:52:54,275
I wanted to tell you the truth,

775
00:52:55,075 --> 00:52:57,945
but I figured one tragedy was enough.

776
00:52:59,145 --> 00:53:00,715
In prison, I prayed.

777
00:53:01,755 --> 00:53:03,315
That you would forget all about this...

778
00:53:04,285 --> 00:53:05,725
and start a new life.

779
00:53:07,425 --> 00:53:09,355
I prayed you'd be freed...

780
00:53:10,565 --> 00:53:11,645
from this living fiery pit.

781
00:53:12,225 --> 00:53:14,995
- What are you trying to say? - But it was no use.

782
00:53:17,435 --> 00:53:19,935
It's been a little over two years now.

783
00:53:20,505 --> 00:53:22,405
It was right after I got out of prison.

784
00:53:27,415 --> 00:53:29,445
When you came at me with that knife,

785
00:53:31,215 --> 00:53:32,615
saying you were going to kill me...

786
00:53:33,755 --> 00:53:35,885
to get revenge for your parents.

787
00:53:37,525 --> 00:53:38,525
Stop it.

788
00:53:39,085 --> 00:53:40,625
You were such a sweet kid,

789
00:53:42,095 --> 00:53:44,225
but you had completely turned into a monster.

790
00:53:46,695 --> 00:53:48,335
I'm sure you were filled with resentment.

791
00:53:49,335 --> 00:53:51,805
- You were orphaned overnight. - Please, just stop.

792
00:53:51,865 --> 00:53:52,865
I can tell...

793
00:53:53,605 --> 00:53:55,205
just by looking into a person's eyes...

794
00:53:57,175 --> 00:54:00,815
whether or not they're truly capable of killing someone.

795
00:54:01,745 --> 00:54:02,745
But when I looked at you,

796
00:54:03,645 --> 00:54:06,015
I knew you were actually capable of killing someone.

797
00:54:07,055 --> 00:54:10,185
- Your revenge made you a monster. - Shut it!

798
00:54:10,725 --> 00:54:13,795
- Just shut it! - Shut your mouth and hear me out!

799
00:54:14,695 --> 00:54:16,695
I haven't even started yet!

800
00:54:21,465 --> 00:54:23,665
I don't care about any of that. Just tell me one thing.

801
00:54:23,765 --> 00:54:25,735
Did you kill my parents?

802
00:54:28,305 --> 00:54:29,305
Myo Jin!

803
00:54:31,005 --> 00:54:32,275
Do you miss your parents?

804
00:54:32,945 --> 00:54:34,845
You won't rest till there's blood, will you?

805
00:54:35,375 --> 00:54:36,815
If you want your revenge,

806
00:54:37,185 --> 00:54:39,085
you need to get your head on straight first!

807
00:54:44,025 --> 00:54:45,485
Start making some sense!

808
00:54:45,755 --> 00:54:49,425
You secretly tailed Ham Myo Jin. You thought you'd score some cash...

809
00:54:49,495 --> 00:54:51,001
and decided to keep it all for yourself?

810
00:54:51,025 --> 00:54:52,401
Are you out of your mind right now?

811
00:54:52,425 --> 00:54:56,665
No, it's just, one thing just led to another.

812
00:54:58,365 --> 00:55:03,145
- Pull this nonsense and you're out. - Hey, what about Ryu Jun Ho?

813
00:55:03,605 --> 00:55:06,945
He's completely in the dark, so you just focus on your part.

814
00:55:07,015 --> 00:55:08,675
Okay, I'll call you when I'm done.

815
00:55:10,745 --> 00:55:12,845
All right. Let's move.

816
00:55:13,415 --> 00:55:15,485
Yeong Gu, get everyone ready.

817
00:55:15,755 --> 00:55:16,755
Yes, boss!

818
00:55:17,585 --> 00:55:19,455
- Get ready! - Ready!

819
00:55:29,765 --> 00:55:30,765
What is that?

820
00:55:34,105 --> 00:55:36,475
What? What do you mean, "out of nowhere"?

821
00:55:36,845 --> 00:55:37,845
Can't you see who it is?

822
00:55:38,245 --> 00:55:40,485
No, it's pitch-black. I can't see a thing. What do I do?

823
00:55:41,275 --> 00:55:44,445
You're saying there's someone else after Ham Myo Jin besides us?

824
00:55:44,515 --> 00:55:46,915
Look, forget it. I'll just ignore them and go in.

825
00:55:47,415 --> 00:55:48,491
We won't get a chance like this again.

826
00:55:48,515 --> 00:55:52,455
Are you crazy? You want to die? Stop this and pull out now!

827
00:55:52,585 --> 00:55:55,171
Some shops are still open nearby. It's likely someone from there.

828
00:55:55,195 --> 00:55:56,725
Why are you freaking out over nothing?

829
00:55:56,795 --> 00:56:00,495
Don't make me repeat myself. Pull out now.

830
00:56:00,565 --> 00:56:03,165
If you don't, we're done. As of right now.

831
00:56:04,665 --> 00:56:05,665
Hey, you...

832
00:56:06,035 --> 00:56:09,575
Hello? That shameless wench. I've let her get away with too much.

833
00:56:09,775 --> 00:56:10,775
Hey! Everyone out!

834
00:56:15,645 --> 00:56:16,991
This'll be super easy, you got it?

835
00:56:17,015 --> 00:56:20,255
The woman from the photo. Grab her and bring her out fast.

836
00:56:20,455 --> 00:56:21,654
- Yes, boss! - Yes, boss!

837
00:56:21,655 --> 00:56:22,855
Let's go.

838
00:56:26,825 --> 00:56:28,231
(It's hard enough to get by! Why force redevelopment?)

839
00:56:28,255 --> 00:56:30,595
(We adamantly oppose this reckless redevelopment.)

840
00:56:33,595 --> 00:56:34,765
Hey, is this the place?

841
00:56:35,065 --> 00:56:36,765
Strange. There's not a soul in sight.

842
00:56:37,265 --> 00:56:39,265
This is the latest model. It's foolproof.

843
00:56:40,705 --> 00:56:41,775
Hey, stop the car.

844
00:56:42,405 --> 00:56:43,475
Looks like someone's here.

845
00:56:56,485 --> 00:56:57,485
What?

846
00:56:58,755 --> 00:57:00,925
That's the car. It belongs to An's goons.

847
00:57:02,395 --> 00:57:03,395
What is that?

848
00:57:03,795 --> 00:57:05,795
When I drug the clients and they start tripping,

849
00:57:06,265 --> 00:57:08,035
An's goons are the ones who come get them.

850
00:57:08,095 --> 00:57:10,235
They always used that exact car to haul them away.

851
00:57:10,435 --> 00:57:12,875
Man, what a pleasant surprise running into these jerks again.

852
00:57:14,275 --> 00:57:16,775
- What? - You're a real genius, you scum.

853
00:57:35,725 --> 00:57:37,201
Wait, how'd you get your hands on that?

854
00:57:37,225 --> 00:57:39,565
I got it from an animal hospital.

855
00:57:45,535 --> 00:57:46,975
What about him? Just leave him here?

856
00:57:48,135 --> 00:57:49,305
Yes, he'll be fine.

857
00:57:50,705 --> 00:57:51,745
Let's make this quick.

858
00:57:57,985 --> 00:58:01,185
By the way, do you even know what An looks like?

859
00:58:01,315 --> 00:58:03,955
How would I know? Have you seen him, boss?

860
00:58:09,995 --> 00:58:12,555
You don't know what he looks like, and you knocked that guy out?

861
00:58:18,005 --> 00:58:19,165
Wake him back up.

862
00:58:19,605 --> 00:58:21,765
You idiot, I've got half a mind to kill you right now.

863
00:58:21,835 --> 00:58:24,345
I'm sorry. I'll wake him up right now.

864
00:58:29,145 --> 00:58:30,685
Get up, you fat pig!

865
00:58:32,485 --> 00:58:33,485
So sleepy.

866
00:58:33,555 --> 00:58:36,085
Cut the nonsense. Get up, or I swear I'll kill you!

867
00:58:40,755 --> 00:58:41,755
What?

868
00:58:53,775 --> 00:58:55,035
And who's that now?

869
00:59:31,945 --> 00:59:36,715
(Reverse)

870
00:59:36,915 --> 00:59:40,255
Still, you should have followed her or at least known where she went!

871
00:59:40,415 --> 00:59:43,755
This person is no pushover. Things could get messy.

872
00:59:43,955 --> 00:59:47,555
- Don't stop. - But what if she gets killed?

873
00:59:47,755 --> 00:59:49,125
This isn't what I've been taking.

874
00:59:49,295 --> 00:59:51,271
Jun Ho said they changed your meds at the hospital.

875
00:59:51,295 --> 00:59:53,125
Do I really need this?

876
00:59:53,435 --> 00:59:55,915
He and her husband are plotting to get rid of her as we speak.

877
00:59:55,995 --> 00:59:57,005
Where's your boss?

878
00:59:57,065 --> 01:00:00,435
What is he getting into with that woman?

879
01:00:00,935 --> 01:00:03,745
So Ham Myo Jin has her own agenda too?
